## KB Storage Routing

Three separate layers — do not mix their content:

| Layer | Path | Write method | Mutable? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Immutable raw | `vault/raw/<type>/<slug>.md` | direct file write | **No** |
| Raw archive | `vault/mcp_raw/<src>/<YYYY-MM-DD>/<id>.md` | `archive_raw` MCP tool | No |
| Canonical KB | `vault/wiki/<category>/<slug>.md` | direct file write | Yes |
| Memory pointers | `vault/memory/<YYYY>/<MM>/<MEM-ID>.md` | `save_memory` MCP tool | Yes |

### vault/raw/ subtrees (immutable source copies)

- `vault/raw/articles/` — web articles and pasted text
- `vault/raw/pdf/` — PDF documents
- `vault/raw/notes/` — manual pre-ingest notes

### vault/wiki/ subtrees (canonical KB)

- `vault/wiki/sources/` — ingested source summaries
- `vault/wiki/concepts/` — extracted concept definitions
- `vault/wiki/entities/` — named entities (people, orgs, products, systems)
- `vault/wiki/analyses/` — structured analyses and comparisons
- `vault/wiki/index.md` — navigation hub; updated on every ingest
- `vault/wiki/log.md` — one-line entry after every ingest or lint run

### save_memory — pointer only

After writing to `vault/wiki/`, call `save_memory` with a **pointer record**:

```yaml
title: "KB: <title>"
content: |
  <3-8 line summary>
  See [[wiki/<category>/<slug>]] for full details.
roles: ["fact"]          # or "summary" for lint/analysis pointers
topics: [<tags>]
tags: ["kb", "<category>"]
raw_refs: [<mcp_id>]     # link to archive_raw id when available
```

**Never** write the full canonical wiki note body into `content`.

## LLM Runtime Policy

- Local LLM provider is fixed to **Ollama**.
- Default endpoint is `http://localhost:11434`. Override with `OLLAMA_BASE_URL`.
- Primary model is `gemma4:e4b` (9.6 GB, 128K context).
- Lightweight tasks use `gemma4:e2b` (7.2 GB, 128K context).
- All skills must call Ollama through `scripts/ollama_kb.py::generate()`. Do not scatter raw `requests.post` calls.
- Default API style is Ollama native `/api/chat`. OpenAI-compatible mode is optional and secondary.
- Timeout is 300 s (configurable via `OLLAMA_TIMEOUT`).
- Shared Ollama request schema, model names, timeout, and error handling must remain identical across all skills — change only in `scripts/ollama_kb.py`.

## Skill Model Assignments

| Skill | Default model | Fallback |
|---|---|---|
| obsidian-ingest | `gemma4:e4b` | — |
| obsidian-query | `gemma4:e4b` | — |
| obsidian-lint | `gemma4:e2b` | `gemma4:e4b` (complex cases) |

## Thinking Mode

- Gemma 4 supports `<|think|>` token-based thinking. Control via system prompt only.
- Do not include previous turn thoughts in history for multi-turn sessions.
